data.value:
Verse 1:
Too many people are tryin' to change me
Too many people are lookin' to rearrange me
But the last thing I'll ever do
To prove that I am a man like you

Verse 2
Is work from nine to five tryin' to keep myself alive
And have to listen every day to everybody's jive
And concentrate my time on simply tryin' to make a dime
And agitate my mind on tryin' to make our values rhyme

Chorus:
Too many things that I've got to do
Too many bags that I've got to run through
And the last thing I'll ever do
To prove that I am a man like you

Bridge:
Is turn away the girls even though I want a whirl
And worry just because that's what everybody else does
And chase myself around so that I'm not called a clown
Wear a suit and tie when I'd rather sit and die

Verse 1:
You want to relax,
All you gotta do is let me do everything,
Just let go of your tasks,
Don't worry, everything will be just fine.

Chorus:
Find yourself inside your mind
Don't be in panic, be relaxed.

Verse 2:
Find your peace, find your strength,
And when you reach your confidence,
Lying down, relaxing, and sensing the nature.

Bridge:
Find that you're not the kind to face the ugliness of reality,
Stay by the truth and we will find the calmness to stay in all its splendid beauty.
Verse 1:
Too many people trying to change me
Looking to attack me verbally
The last thing I'll ever do
Is to please narrow-minded people like you

Pre-Chorus:
You're too weak trying to please the masses
Looking to conform to the mainstream

Chorus:
Too many things that I got to beware
Social rules that I got to run through
The last thing I'll ever do
Is to prove that I am thinking like you

Verse 2:
Working from nine to five trying to keep myself alive
Listening everyday to what people want to talk about
Concentrating my time on just trying to make a dime
Agitating my mind on trying to make my mind to match the reality

Pre-Chorus:
You're too weak trying to please everyone
Looking to conform to stereotypes

Bridge:
Turning away the girls even though I want a wife
Worrying just because I feel incomplete
Doing what women want so that I'm not called a clown
Wearing a suit and tie when I'd rather sit and die
Verse 3:
City lights shining in the dark
Don't worry it's just life
Their trust have reached balance
You'll find you'll have a lovely time

source: The last thing I'll ever do
Is to prove that I am thinking like you

suggestion.content:
My mind's open, divergent and free,
I'll be myself, can't be someone to please.

I won't conform, I won't give in,
I'll stay true, won't change for no one's win.

I'll play my guitar, break all the rules,
I'll speak my truth, won't be anyone's tool.

suggestion.style: Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five
suggestion.content:
I'll speak up, won't just go with the flow,
My voice is powerful, I'll let it show.

I'll stand firm, won't be swayed,
Babylon system, I will not aid.

My words will cut, like a sharp knife,
I'll speak my mind, won't hide behind a lie.

I'll march to the beat of my own drum,
I won't back down, won't succumb.

I'll break on through to the other side,
Won't be blinded by pressures to abide.

I won't conform to society's ways,
I'll find my own path, won't just run on a maze.

I won't be silenced, I'll speak my truth,
I'll fight for justice, won't just sit and soothe.

I'll use my voice to spread love and light,
Won't conform to hate, won't give in to the fight.

I'll break the chains, won't be told what to do,
I'll stand tall, won't be a puppet for you.

I'll walk my own path, won't follow the trends,
Won't change my ways, won't just pretend.

I'll fly high, won't be bound by the ground,
I'll make my own rules, won't let others drown.

I'll spread my wings, won't be held down,
I'll soar to new heights, won't let anyone's frown.

I'll speak my truth, won't be afraid,
I'll pave my own way, won't let society's norms invade.

I'll stand my ground, won't just go with the flow,
I'll make my own destiny, won't let anyone's expectations grow.

I'll sing my own song, won't imitate,
I'll stay authentic, won't just try to compensate.

parts.name: Verse 2
source: Working from nine to five trying to keep myself alive
Listening everyday to what people want to talk about
Concentrating my time on just trying to make a dime
Agitating my mind on trying to make my mind to match the reality
ai_source: To survive, I work hard every day
Gossip surrounds me, can't escape their play
Money on my mind, chasing dollars and cents
Reality hard to match, sense of contentment

source: Working hard just to stay alive
Hearing gossip every single day

suggestion.content:
Working hard to survive,
Gossip heard daily alive.

Survival's hard work,
Hearing gossip every day's work.

Every day keep going,
Gossiping never slowing.

suggestion.style: Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five
suggestion.content:
Surviving's a struggle,
Gossiping ain't subtle.

Working to stay strong,
Gossip's always wrong.

Survival seems rough,
Gossip never enough.

Working for tomorrow,
Gossip brings sorrow.

Struggling day and night,
Gossip's continuous blight.

Surviving takes strength,
Gossip's at any length.

Working hard every day,
Gossip never goes away.

Surviving's a tough fight,
Gossip's never right.

Working hard to overcome,
Gossiping always succumbs.

Surviving to make it big,
Gossip's just a tiny gig.

Working towards a goal,
Gossip takes its toll.

Struggling to stay alive,
Gossiping is a daily dive.

Surviving in the fame,
Gossip's always the same.

Working hard to get by,
Gossip's just a little lie.

Surviving and thriving,
Gossip never stops striving.
